        <section id="conclusion-overview" class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold border-b-2 border-accent-color pb-2 mb-8">Conclusion & Further Inquiry (Overview)</h2>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">The archetype of ascension represents one of the most persistent aspirations of the human spirit. This report has traced its trajectory from ancient struggles with mortality to the intricate soteriological systems of world religions and the technological ambitions of transhumanism. The theoretical profile of the *Corpus Divinum* serves as a synthetic ideal—a thought experiment bridging spiritual aspirations with speculative science.</p>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">This synthesis suggests several avenues for future interdisciplinary inquiry: experimental investigation into macroscopic quantum coherence in biological systems; advanced research into biophoton emissions in relation to altered states of consciousness; and the development of a "noetic physics" that treats consciousness as a fundamental component of reality.[130, 131, 142, 127, 159] By pursuing these lines of inquiry, we may find that the ancient dream of ascension is not merely a myth to be interpreted, but a potentiality to be explored.</p>
        </section>

